HEADWORD: Atheist
<hw>A"the*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ without god;
<grk>'a</grk> priv. + <?/ god: cf. F. <ets>ath⟦eacute⟧iste</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who disbelieves or denies the existence of a God,
or supreme intelligent Being.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A godless person.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Infidel; unbeliever.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>See <er>Infidel</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

